Domain Description – Peer-to-Peer Marketplace
This database supports a peer-to-peer marketplace where users can browse, post, and save listings. It is structured around five core tables.

- USER TABLE is the backbone of the system: it stores each user's unique identifier, their name, and email address, allowing the platform to manage accounts and link activity
back to individuals.

- POSTS TABLE holds all marketplace listings: when a user decides to sell something, their listing is recorded here with a unique ID, a price, a category reference, and a 
description of the item. The table also tracks when the listing was created and includes a boolean flag that the backend uses to mark a post as expired once it passes a set time limit.

- CATEGORIES TABLE keeps things organised on the browsing side. By grouping posts into categories, it makes it easier for users to navigate the marketplace and find what 
they're looking for without scrolling through unrelated listings.

- MEDIA TABLE handles images. Since sellers typically upload more than one photo of their item, this table provides a centralised place to store all pictures associated 
with a given post, linked back to it by the post's ID.

- FAVOURITES TABLE lets users save listings they're interested in; whether to revisit later or compare against other options. It ties a user to a post, creating a lightweight
bookmarking system within the platform.
